      <abstract>
        <p>Cutaneous larva migrans is a pruritic dermatitis due to the inoculation of helminths
larvae in the skin, and it often occurs in children in tropical and subtropical
areas. The authors describe an atypical case of cutaneous larva migrans in a 11
year-old child with scalp involvement, an unusual topography for this lesion.</p>
      </abstract>
